The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                               IN THE CITY
                  
	 The Indian Football Association (IFA) will have a meeting with the Cricket Association of Bengal (CAB) officials on Thursday to discuss the grounds issue. The Calcutta Football League matches on the enclosed grounds have created a problem for the local cricket season and hopefully Thursdays meeting will see a solution. The IFA will also meet the three I-League clubs following a fresh directive from the All India Football Federation on the minimal use of I-League players during the CFL.          
	 Andorra captain Oscar Sonajee, who was on trials for the Churchill Brothers, failed to impress coach Carlos Perreira and will be reaching the city on Thursday for a trial with East Bengal.                 
	 Umang Sharma of Uttar Pradesh scored an unbeaten 84 as the visitors reached a comfortable 268 for 3 against Bengal at stumps on Day I in their CK Nayudu (U-22) Trophy match at Jadavpur University, Salt Lake Campus ground. Meanwhile, Bengal opener Rohan Banerjee injured his finger while fielding, but an X-ray revealed there was no fracture.      
	Brief scores: UP 268/3 (U Sharma 84*) vs Bengal. Match to continue            
	Football: CFL  Md Sp. vs CPT at Md Sp. ground from 2.30pm                                                                                                                                                                       
